# MASLOW-App — Cline/Cursor Rules

## EAS Build + Submit (CRITICAL)
Building and submitting to TestFlight are TWO SEPARATE STEPS.

- `eas build --platform ios --profile production` → compiles the IPA only
- `eas submit --platform ios --latest` → submits the most recent build to Apple

NEVER rebuild just to resubmit. If a build already exists, use `eas submit --latest`.
Do NOT chain build + submit automatically unless explicitly asked.
After a successful submit, confirm to the user: "Submitted build [number] to Apple. TestFlight email typically arrives within 30-60 minutes."

## Commit Messages
Do NOT add "Co-Authored-By: Claude" or any Co-Authored-By lines to commit messages.

## General
- MVP first. Do not add unrequested features.
- Always confirm scope before starting large changes.
- Ask before installing new packages.
